body:
### Description

`Alpha` channel is not working as expected when `red`, `green` and `blue` are 0 with drawing rectangle on `SKSvgCanvas` but works fine with `SKSurface`.

I found a workaround for this issue, simple ensure at least one color (`red`, `green` or `blue`) is greater then 0, then apha is working with `SKSvgCanvas`.

### Code

Here a like code to reproduce the bug:
```cs
using SkiaSharp;
using System.IO;

using var stream = new FileStream("Test.svg", FileMode.Create);
var rect = new SKRect(0, 0, 100, 100);

var rect1 = new SKRect(15, 15, 95, 95);
var rect2 = new SKRect(10, 10, 80, 80);

var info = new SKImageInfo(
                width: 100,
                height: 100,
                colorType: SKColorType.Rgba8888,
                alphaType: SKAlphaType.Premul);

using var svg = SKSvgCanvas.Create(rect, stream);
var surface = SKSurface.Create(info);

var color1 = new SKColor(red: 0, green: 0, blue: 0, alpha: 128);
var color2 = new SKColor(red: 0, green: 0, blue: 0, alpha: 255);

var paint1 = new SKPaint() { Color = color1, IsStroke = false, IsAntialias = true };
var paint2 = new SKPaint() { Color = color2, IsStroke = false, IsAntialias = true };

surface.Canvas.DrawRect(rect1, paint1);
surface.Canvas.DrawRect(rect2, paint2);

svg.DrawRect(rect1, paint1);
svg.DrawRect(rect2, paint2);

var image = surface.Snapshot();
var skData = image.Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 100);
File.WriteAllBytes("Test.png", skData.ToArray());

```


### Expected Behavior

The `PNG` output is corrected but on the `SVG` output, booth rectangle are black!

